<p>Council bosses argue they needed tougher measures across the region to prevent a full-blown lockdown and save lives. </p>

<p>Labour MPs in the North East welcomed the new measures outlined by Mr Hancock, while urging the Government to work better with local councils.</p>

<p>In a joint letter to the minister, they said: 'We do (...) believe that this must be done in close collaboration with local authorities, who must have access to all appropriate information, data and support in order to make the best decisions for their areas.'</p>

<p>Mr Hancock's announcement came after measures in the likes of Greater Manchester and Birmingham were put in place in a bid to address rising rates of infection.</p>

