<p>She asked: 'Can the Prime Minister confirm yes or no, do all care homes in this country have weekly tests?'</p>

<p>Mr Johnson replied: 'Yes, to the best of my knowledge care homes in this country… should get weekly tests for all staff members and tests every 28 days for those who are in the care homes, the residents in the care homes.'</p>

<p>The premier also complained that Labour was 'carping from the sidelines' while the government tried to deal with 'one of the most difficult dilemmas' ever faced by any administration. </p>

<p>Appearing before the education select committee today, Gavin Williamson revealed he had met the government's Test &amp; Trace tsar Baroness Harding this week to insist there must be 'swift' screening available for schools.</p>

